      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's quite a bit to take in. If these variations are actually being noted in studies—like the bone density in Caucasians or the fiber types in Black and Asian populations—doesn't that mean we should almost be grouping clients by these biological predispositions rather than just individual fitness levels? Like, if a client is of a certain descent, is it more \"scientifically sound\" to assume certain physical limits or strengths right from the start to save time on testing?",
